12 piece French Macarons
3.5 ounce SkinnyDipped Dark Chocolate Peppermint Almonds
4 unit Butter Toffee Bundt Cakes
4 unit Chocolate Caramel Lava Cakes

Bundt Cakes:
1. Keep frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 3 days. If frozen, thaw in the refrigerator (at 40 degrees) overnight or at room temperature for 2-3 hours before eating.
2. RECOMMENDED: Remove plastic wrap from trays; microwave until warmed through, 50-60 seconds for Butter Toffee Bundt Cakes or 35-45 seconds for Filled Chocolate Bundt Cakes. (Do not overheat.) Let cakes cool 1-2 minutes, then turn out onto plates and serve.
3. OVEN ALTERNATIVE: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Remove plastic wrap from trays; place on a baking sheet and bake until warmed through, 14-16 minutes for Butter Toffee Bundt Cakes or 15-17 minutes for Filled Chocolate Bundt Cakes. (Note: Oven times may vary.) Let cakes cool 1-2 minutes, then turn out onto plates and serve.

Macarons & Peppermint Almonds:
Enjoy!